post_text:
Another Track season is in the history books. Congratulations to Shania Nahring and Gavin Makela on ending their season at the Section 5A meet. Even though they won't be competing at State next weekend we are very proud of them.
Next season looks to be very promising as the 6th through 11th grade athletes made tremendous improvement this season. They are really making a difference and are making the OHS Track future look very bright.
As coaches Brenda, Jay and I are extremely proud of these fine young men and women. Have a good summer.

post_text:
Congratulations to the girls' 7th grade and JV track teams for winning last night's Great River Conference Meet!!! The 7th grade boys' team were Runner Up! The boys' 8th grade and JV teams placed 4th and the 8th grade girls team placed 5th.

Conference Champs in their events were Haileigh Bolling, Izzy Warren, Tatum Peterson, Kailey Arnold, Alyssa Lang, Annie Rodenborg, Katie Kunst, Racheal Molin, Alivia Sanborn, Melissa Bartel, Annika Berg, Brandee Bolz, Olivia Hudoba, Bryce Beier, Andy Berg, Jon Brasch, Asher Gray, Rhett Hudoba and Ethan Warren!

Great job to all of our JH/JV athletes this season! We had a very successful year with many, many new personal records and lots of memories made. The Ogilvie Track program has a very promising future!

Good luck to Shania Nahring and Gavin Makela at next week's Section Meet!

We had a smaller meet last night April 25. One of the other teams brought some new inexperienced High Jump competitors. A couple of our athletes, Shania Nahring and Annika Berg, gave them some pointers and encouragement.
This morning I received this small note from the young athletes coach that deserves to be shared "Thanks for having us tonight. We appreciated the invite and hospitality of your staff, athletes and coaches. My young girls will always remember the fine leadership of your girl high jumpers and their positive words of encouragement. Their enthusiasm, and character was amazing".
This is what sports are suppose to be about. Thank you Shania and Annika for making us proud!!

The Teams had a good first meet at the GRC Indoor meet on April 1. For the Girls. Shania Nahring placed in four events, First in Long Jump ( new GRC Indoor record), second in the 55 meter dash, second in the high jump and fifth in the Sprint Medley. Olivia Hudoba was 7th in the 400 M dash. The Sprint Medley team of Bonnie Carlson, Annika Berg, Shania Nahring and Alivia Sanborn was 5th.
For the Boys Seth Lindberg placed 3rd in the 55 m dash, 4th in the Triple Jump, and 4th in the long jump. Gavin Makela was 4th in the 55 m dash. Seth Lombard was 3rd in the Shot Put. Jon Brasch was 6th in the 400 m dash. The Sprint Medley team of Ethan Warren, Seth Lindberg, Seth Lombard and Gavin Makel was 2nd. The 800 m relay team of Rhett Hudoba, Andy Berg, Alex VnderVegt and Asher Gray placed 4th.
Our next meet is Thursday April 6 at home.
